---
description: Rust and Tauri backend rules
globs: ["src-tauri/src/**/*.rs"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Backend responsibilities:
- Git CLI execution
- filesystem and OS interaction
- secure settings and sensitive operations
- parsing command output
- AI provider orchestration where applicable

Rules:
- Keep Tauri command handlers thin.
- Move reusable logic into services or infrastructure modules.
- Use typed DTOs for command input/output.
- Use serde-friendly structs consistently.
- Return typed errors, not ad-hoc strings.
- Never shell-interpolate user input.
- Always pass command arguments as separate args.
- Set explicit current_dir for repo-scoped Git operations.
- Handle timeouts and command failures safely.
- Parse machine-friendly Git output where possible.
- Prefer testable pure parsers for Git output transformation.

Error rules:
- map external failures to stable error codes
- include human-readable message plus optional details
- mark recoverable vs unrecoverable errors when possible

Security rules:
- do not log secrets or raw tokens
- do not expose provider credentials to the frontend
- do not send repository content to AI unless that flow is explicitly enabled